{
  "texts": [
    "First, as long as the distortion-minimizing embedding framework is relevant, it is still feasible to extend the suggested concepts to other data domains, including the JPEG image domain, the unnatural image domain, or even the audio domain.",
    "Second, adding the paired loss to GAN-based steganography techniques could enhance their overall robustness and performance.",
    "Third, the suggested adversarial steganography approach may determine the payload capacity for each image by eliminating the assumed payload rate constraint for each image.",
    "This approach can help steganographers address the payload allocation issue in batch steganography scenarios.",
    "Furthermore, Lin et al. [99] noticed many studies and proposals on different learning models, attack strategies, and defense tactics that are available in the literature."
  ]
